<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="535" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1532,2027]" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1532,1559]" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope with distinct median and sublateral carinae. Forewings with very weak knee prominence. Hind tibia with two lateral spines. Aedeagus with ventral hooks curved at right angle. Style with weakly concave hind margin and with a comb under the capitulum; capitulum on short neck. Total length: male—3.5 mm, females—3.8– 4.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="537" pageId="18" pageNumber="535" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1532,2027]" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1676,1703]" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">Description.</emphasis>
Metope flat (almost not visible from above), wide, weakly enlarged below eyes, with distinct median and sublateral carinae (
<figureCitation box="[464,550,1712,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">Figs 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[562,593,1712,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-28@16.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–55. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691503/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">53</figureCitation>
). Median carina of metope running from its upper margin to metopoclypeal suture. Sublateral carinae of metope not reaching metopoclypeal suture. Coryphe transverse, twice as wide as long medially; anterior margin widely convex; posterior margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[920,996,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">Fig 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1008,1040,1784,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-28@16.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–55. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691503/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">55</figureCitation>
). Pronotum slightly longer than coryphe, sometimes with weak median carina. Mesonotum slightly longer than pronotum, without carinae. Forewings nearly oval, with many transverse veins in its apical halves. Basal cell circular. Radius and media of forewings diverging from the basal cell at acute angle and furcating at wing basal third; radius furcating before media. Forewing vein sequence (
<figureCitation box="[326,411,1928,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
): R 3 (R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[510,518,1947,1961]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">1</subScript>
not reaching wing margin); M 6, firstly furcating at wing basal third, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1339,1347,1947,1961]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1947,1961]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="535">2</subScript>
furcating at wing middle and apically; CuA1. Hind tibia with two lateral spines and 9–10 apical spines. First metatarsomere with seven intermediate spines.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691517" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6691517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691517/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" startId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" targetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1708,1841]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1708,1733]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">FIGURES 71–77.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[349,513,1709,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[349,460,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">Lethierium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, ovipositor structure, 71–75— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bergevin, 1915)" baseAuthorityName="Bergevin" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[826,1120,1709,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperi">
<emphasis box="[826,935,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">L. juniperi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bergevin" box="[950,1112,1709,1733]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" pagination="71 - 77" refId="ref8660" refString="Bergevin, de E. (1915) Description de deux espece nouvelles d' Hysteropterum (Hemipt., Issidae) de l'Afrique du Nord. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord, 7, 71 - 77." type="journal article" year="1915">Bergevin, 1915</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, Aïn Kerma, 76–77— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dlabola, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Hysteropterum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">L. cedricolum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J." box="[229,380,1745,1769]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536" pagination="21 - 59" refId="ref8826" refString="Dlabola, J. (1989) Neue Issiden und andere Zikadenarten des Mediterraneums und vom zuliegenden Eremial (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45 B (1), 21 - 59." type="journal article" year="1989">Dlabola, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1887,2021]" box="[199,1437,1887,1913]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1887,1913]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">Coloration.</emphasis>
General coloration light brown to straw yellow. Rostrum dark brown, with black 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1312,1326,1887,1901]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">rd</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1887,2021]" box="[151,1436,1923,1949]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">Abdominal tergites brown to dark brown, with yellow hind margins, to black. Sensory pits of abdominal sternites</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1887,2021]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,150,609]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="537" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">
IV–VI surrounded by brown to dark brown areas. Claws brown to dark brown. Apices of leg spines black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,535,1994,2021]" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[388,520,1994,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="536">Figs 56–63</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Anal tube elongate, twice as long as wide medially, its lateral margins steeply turned down apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[597,682,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), with semicircular subapical processes (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1424,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Anal column large, ⅓ of anal tube length. Phallobase with large lobe-shaped processes at its basement, concaved or truncated (
<figureCitation box="[271,355,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Ventral phallobase lobe notched apically (
<figureCitation box="[844,927,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with curved at right angle ventral hooks. Style with weakly concave hind margin and with a comb under the capitulum; caudo-dorsal angle truncate (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Capitulum of style on short neck, narrowing apically (in dorsal view), with large lateral and apical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–63" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,532,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-160@17.[151,1436,524,1655]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 56–63. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 56—pygofer, lateral view; 57—anal tube, lateral view; 58—anal tube, dorsal view; 59—penis and connective, lateral view; 60—connective, caudal view; 61—penis, ventral view; 62—style, lateral view; 63—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691509/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,599,366,393]" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[411,499,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Figs 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[512,583,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691513/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">69, 70</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Hind margin of sternite VII widely concave, with short labial median process (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[405,492,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691513/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Anal tube convex (in lateral view); parallel-sided, almost not narrowing apically, twice as long as wide medially, widely rounded apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[995,1083,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">Figs 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1097,1129,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691513/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="537">69</figureCitation>
). Anal column short, ¹⁄ of length of anal tube, narrow.
</paragraph>
